<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD965BFFF2FF27151A3BEDF9A8" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965BFFF2FF27151A3AF0F9EA" blockId="2.[178,1085,1402,1541]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">
<taxonomicName id="4C37D0B5965BFFF2FF27151A3820FA60" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[178,303,1402,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B9437724965BFFF2FF27151A3820FA60" box="[178,303,1402,1423]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">P. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the commonest and most widespread member of the genus. These new records extends its range yet much further east from Celebes and the 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FC3915F73D11FA42" box="[940,1054,1431,1453]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Philippines</collectingCountry>
to western (Irian Jaya) and eastern (Papua) New 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FD1215D43BDCFA25" box="[647,723,1460,1482]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. The specimens from Dory (spelled ‘Dorey’ in Wallace’s &quot;The Malay Archipelago&quot;), the site of present-day Manokwari in Irian Jaya, were collected by Alfred Russel Wallace between 
<date id="FF898DF6965BFFF2FCB7158F3AF3F9EA" box="[802,1020,1519,1541]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" value="1858-03" valueMax="1858-07-31" valueMin="1858-03-00">March and July 1858</date>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965BFFF2FF2716743BEDF9A8" blockId="2.[178,1086,1556,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">
Twenty-four other specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FDA116743B64F9C5" box="[564,619,1556,1578]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FDEE16743BE7F9C5" box="[635,744,1556,1578]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, West 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FCAC16743A97F9C5" box="[825,920,1556,1578]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FC3C16743D04F9C5" box="[937,1035,1556,1578]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FF2716513806F9A8" box="[178,265,1585,1607]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
were found in the Geneva museum collection.
</paragraph>
